            <title><![CDATA[KILLER INN closed beta test set for July 25 to 28]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/killer-inn-closed-beta-test-set-for-july-25-to-28</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/killer-inn-closed-beta-test-set-for-july-25-to-28.1250619/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

    <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/pc">PC</a></li>    </ul>

    
    <p><span>Test play the multiplayer murder mystery action game.</span>
      </p></div><div><p>Publisher and developer <a title="Companies > Square Enix [5,358 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/square-enix">Square Enix</a>, and developer <a title="Companies > Tactic Studios [1 article]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/tactic-studios">Tactic Studios</a> will run a closed beta test for <a title="Genres > Multiplayer [555 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/multiplayer">multiplayer</a> murder mystery <a title="Genres > Action [2,883 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/action">action game</a> <a title="Games > KILLER INN [1 article]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/killer-inn">KILLER INN</a> from <a href="https://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?iso=20250725T2200" target="_blank">July 25 at 3:00 p.m. PT / 6:00 p.m. ET</a> to <a href="https://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?iso=20250728T2159" target="_blank">July 28 at 2:59 p.m. PT / 5:59 p.m. ET</a>, the companies <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/news/app/1598230/view/508460478830215455" target="_blank">announced</a>. Users can request access to the test via the game’s <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1598230/KILLER_INN/" target="_blank">Steam page</a>. <span id="more-979597"></span></p><p>“This first test is geared toward testing the game’s network and servers to ensure a smooth and enjoyable experience for players,” reads the announcement. “<em>KILLER INN</em> is still in development, so you may experience unexpected issues, network latency, or performance drops. Also, we’re currently working on tutorials that guide you through <em>KILLER INN</em>’s unique game rules and mechanics, but these will not be included in this beta test. So, to get the most out of your time with <em>KILLER INN</em>, we recommend familiarizing yourself with the game before the start of the beta.”</p><p><em>KILLER INN</em> will be available for <a title="Platforms > PC [23,714 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/pc">PC</a> via <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1598230/KILLER_INN/" target="_blank">Steam</a>. A release date has yet to be announced.</p></div></div><br/><br/>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/killer-inn-closed-beta-test-set-for-july-25-to-28]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Puzzle platformer The Elf on the Shelf: Christmas Heroes announced for PS5, Xbox Series, PS4, Xbox One, Switch, and PC]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/puzzle-platformer-the-elf-on-the-shelf-christmas-heroes-announced-for-ps5-xbox-series-ps4-xbox-one-switch-and-pc</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/puzzle-platformer-the-elf-on-the-shelf-christmas-heroes-announced-for-ps5-xbox-series-ps4-xbox-one-switch-and-pc.1250616/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><p>Publisher <a title="Companies > Outright Games [25 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/outright-games">Outright Games</a> and developer <a title="Companies > Casual Brothers [2 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/casual-brothers">Casual Brothers</a>, in cooperation with The Lumistella Company, have announced puzzle <a title="Genres > Platformer [710 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/platformer">platformer</a> <em><a title="Games > The Elf on the Shelf: Christmas Heroes" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/the-elf-on-the-shelf-christmas-heroes">The Elf on the Shelf: Christmas Heroes</a></em> for <a title="Platforms > PS5 [9,940 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps5">PlayStation 5</a>, <a title="Platforms > Xbox Series [7,557 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/xbox/xbox-series">Xbox Series</a>, <a title="Platforms > PS4 [28,177 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps4">PlayStation 4</a>, <a title="Platforms > Xbox One [14,077 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/xbox/xbox-one">Xbox One</a>, <a title="Platforms > Switch [17,371 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch">Switch</a>, and <a title="Platforms > PC [23,714 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/pc">PC</a> (<a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/3210120/The_Elf_on_the_Shelf_Christmas_Heroes/" target="_blank">Steam</a>, Microsoft Store). It will launch on October 17. <span id="more-979577"></span></p><p>“Over the last two decades, The Elf on the Shelf has become a treasured part of the holiday season for so many families around the world,” said The Lumistella Company co-founder and co-CEO Chanda Bell in a press release. “From playful moments to heartfelt memories, the tradition brings people together in meaningful ways. Through the launch of <em>Christmas Heroes</em>, we’re excited to offer a new way for families to engage with the magic, inviting them to create more joyful traditions and experience the North Pole like never before.” </p><p>Outright Games managing director Stephanie Malham added, “We’re delighted to team up with The Lumistella Company to turn a cherished holiday tradition into an engaging, interactive journey. Our goal was to make a game that feels like opening the door to Santa’s workshop. The world of The Elf on the Shelf is so rich with charm and curiosity, we wanted to pack every level with that same playful energy. It’s a game full of heart, humor, and holiday magic, where kids and their families can feel like true Christmas heroes.”</p><p>Here is an overview of the game, via Outright Games:</p><blockquote><p><strong>About</strong></p><p>Do you believe in Christmas magic? You’ll need every bit to help Santa save Christmas! With Christmas Spirit running low, the North Pole isn’t so merry. Santa’s sleigh won’t fly, gifts aren’t ready, and there’s a chance that nice children might not end up on Santa’s Nice List.</p><!-- AD: content -->
        <p>Dash, swing, and leap through training to become an “official Scout Elf”! Pick your most festive outfit and spread cheer as you explore every room, dodge obstacles, and add sparkle to each corner of the home.</p><p>This season, pledge to make things merry and bright. Are you ready to be a Christmas Hero?</p><p><strong>Key Features</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Enjoy a Christmas Tradition</strong> – Follow the story or enjoy minigames—there’s holiday fun for everyone.</li><li><strong>Become a Scout Elf</strong> –&nbsp;Complete training and help Santa with his Nice List.</li><li><strong>Play Minigames Filled With Magic</strong> – Solve puzzles, match cards, sort ornaments and explore enchanted mazes.</li><li><strong>Collect and Shine</strong> – Run, jump, and swing to gather rewards. If you miss a few, dive back into the fun to collect them all.</li><li><strong>Design Your Scout Elf Hero</strong> – Create the perfect holiday outfit with sparkling seasonal accessories.</li></ul></blockquote><p>Watch the announcement trailer below.</p><h2><span>Announce Trailer</span></h2><p><iframe title="The Elf on the Shelf ®: Christmas Heroes| Announce Trailer | US | ESRB" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/9_mVWU3N7B4?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></p></div></div><br/><br/>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/puzzle-platformer-the-elf-on-the-shelf-christmas-heroes-announced-for-ps5-xbox-series-ps4-xbox-one-switch-and-pc]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[LoveR Kiss: Endless Memories adds Switch 2 version]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/lover-kiss-endless-memories-adds-switch-2-version</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/lover-kiss-endless-memories-adds-switch-2-version.1250541/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

    <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch-2">Switch 2</a></li>    </ul>

    
    <p><span>Higher resolution and improved frame rates.</span>
      </p></div><div><p>A <a title="Platforms > Switch 2 [249 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch-2">Switch 2</a> version of <em>Lover Kiss: <a title="Games > Endless Memories [4 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/endless-memories">Endless Memories</a></em> is in development alongside its <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/lover-kiss-endless-memories-announced-for-switch-pc">previously announced</a> Switch and PC (Steam) versions, developer <a title="Companies > Dragami Games [40 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/extreme/dragami-games">Dragami Games</a> announced. <span id="more-979531"></span></p><p>While the Switch and PC versions are due out on November 27 in Japan with support for English, Japanese, and Traditional Chinese language options, a release date for the Switch 2 version was not announced. The press release labels the Switch 2 version a “Nintendo Switch 2 Edition,” suggesting it will at least be available as an upgrade from the Switch version. The Switch 2 version will feature a higher resolution and improved frame rates.</p><p>Outside of the Switch 2 version, Dragami Games also introduced the game’s Switch limited edition and various retailer-specific bonuses as part of the latest “Yukkuri LoveR” video, as well as a look at all the “Magical Heroines” in addition to Magical Yumina.</p><p>Watch the latest “Yukkuri LoveR” video below.</p><h2><span>Yukkuri LoveR: Nintendo Switch 2 Edition in Development!</span></h2><p><iframe title="【LoveR Kiss Endless Memories】Nintendo Switch 2 Edition 鋭意開発中！！【ゆっくりLoveR】" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/kr-vxInH9qg?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></p><!-- AD: content -->
        </div></div><br/><br/>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/lover-kiss-endless-memories-adds-switch-2-version]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Borderlands 4 for Switch 2 launches October 3]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/borderlands-4-for-switch-2-launches-october-3</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/borderlands-4-for-switch-2-launches-october-3.1250508/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

    <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch-2">Switch 2</a></li>    </ul>

    
    <p><span>Just under a month after the PlayStation 5, Xbox Series, and PC versions.</span>
      </p></div><div><p>The <a title="Platforms > Switch 2 [249 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch-2">Switch 2</a> version of <em><a title="Games > Borderlands 4 [10 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/borderlands-4">Borderlands 4</a></em> will launch on October 3, publisher <a title="Companies > 2K [668 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/take-two-interactive-software/2k">2K</a> and developer <a title="Companies > Gearbox Software [244 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/the-gearbox-entertainment-company/gearbox-software">Gearbox Software</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/duvalmagic/status/1947702377185763768" target="_blank">announced</a>. <span id="more-979386"></span></p><p><em>Borderlands 4</em> is due out first for PlayStation 5, Xbox Series, and PC via <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1285190/Borderlands_4/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Steam</a> and <a href="https://store.epicgames.com/p/borderlands-4" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Epic Games Store</a> on September 12.</p><p>Here is an overview of the game, via 2K:</p><blockquote><p><em>Borderlands 4</em> brings intense action, badass Vault Hunters, and billions of wild and deadly weapons to an all-new planet ruled by a ruthless tyrant.</p><p>Crash into Kairos as one of four new Vault Hunters seeking wealth and glory. Wield powerful Action Skills, customize your build with deep skill trees, and dominate enemies with dynamic movement abilities.</p><p>Break free from the oppressive Timekeeper, a ruthless dictator who dominates the masses from on high. Now a world-altering catastrophe threatens his perfect Order, unleashing mayhem across the planet.</p><!-- AD: content -->
        <p>Ignite a resistance and blast your way through mechanical monstrosities, bloodthirsty bandits, and vicious beasts. Amass an arsenal of death-dealing firepower to wreak havoc as you tear your way across Kairos.</p><p>Fight solo or in cooperative play (two-player split-screen or up to four-player online) in this immense science-fiction adventure, packed with free-form combat and exploration, pulse-pounding boss fights, infinitely varied loot drops, and an eclectic cast of unforgettable characters new and old.</p></blockquote></div></div><br/><br/>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/borderlands-4-for-switch-2-launches-october-3]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Terminator 2D: NO FATE delayed to October 31]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/terminator-2d-no-fate-delayed-to-october-31</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/terminator-2d-no-fate-delayed-to-october-31.1250505/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

    <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/pc">PC</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps4">PS4</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps5">PS5</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch">Switch</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/xbox/xbox-one">Xbox One</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/xbox/xbox-series">Xbox Series</a></li>    </ul>

    
    <p><span>No longer due out on September 5.</span>
      </p></div><div><p>Publisher <a title="Companies > Reef Entertainment [8 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/reef-entertainment">Reef Entertainment</a> and developer <a title="Companies > Bitmap Bureau [3 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/bitmap-bureau">Bitmap Bureau</a> have delayed <a title="Genres > Side-Scrolling [1,047 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/side-scrolling">side-scrolling</a> <a title="Genres > Action [2,883 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/action">action game</a> <em><a title="Games > Terminator 2D: NO FATE [2 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/terminator-2d-no-fate">Terminator 2D: NO FATE</a></em> from its <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/02/side-scrolling-action-game-terminator-2d-no-fate-announced-for-ps5-xbox-series-ps4-xbox-one-switch-and-pc">previously planned</a> September 5 release date to October 31. It will be available for <a title="Platforms > PS5 [9,940 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps5">PlayStation 5</a>, <a title="Platforms > Xbox Series [7,557 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/xbox/xbox-series">Xbox Series</a>, <a title="Platforms > PS4 [28,177 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps4">PlayStation 4</a>, <a title="Platforms > Xbox One [14,077 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/xbox/xbox-one">Xbox One</a>, <a title="Platforms > Switch [17,371 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch">Switch</a>, and <a title="Platforms > PC [23,714 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/pc">PC</a> via <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1718460/Terminator_2D_NO_FATE/" target="_blank">Steam</a> and <a href="https://store.epicgames.com/p/terminator-2d-no-fate-e2e134" target="_blank">Epic Games Store</a>. <span id="more-979472"></span></p><p>“Coordinating and manufacturing the physical release has been a longer process than we anticipated, and as a result, we’ve had to delay the release of the game,” Bitmap Bureau said in the delay announcement. “We apologize, and thank you for bearing with us.”</p><p>“This delay will also give the team at Bitmap Bureau extra time to apply some final polish to the game itself and we would like all players to have the opportunity to experience the best version of <em>Terminator 2D: NO FATE</em> together. As such, this delay will apply to both physical and digital versions of the game.”</p><p>Here is an overview of the game, via its <a href="https://www.terminator2d.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">official website</a>:</p><blockquote><p><strong>About</strong></p><p>Play as Sarah Connor and the T-800 through a variety of thrilling missions as they take on the T-1000 and try to put a stop to Skynet’s plans before the human race is annihilated. Lead the Resistance as John Connor in the future, fighting on the front lines as mankind’s only hope in the War Against the Machines. In this unique story blending iconic scenes from <em>Terminator 2: Judgment Day</em> with original scenarios and multiple endings, humanity’s fate is yours to decide.​</p><!-- AD: content -->
        <p><em>Terminator 2D: NO FATE</em> brings the groundbreaking action movie to life with the trademark adrenaline-pumping <a title="Genres > Arcade [82 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/arcade">arcade game</a>play and glorious pixel artwork the Bitmap Bureau team are known for.</p><p><strong>Key Features</strong></p><ul><li>Step into a classic arcade experience that pays homage to the Terminator universe with authentic arcade gameplay, music and visuals built from the ground up.​​</li><li>Relive iconic moments and forge new paths as Sarah, John and the T-800 in a narrative featuring a mix of classic T2: Judgment Day scenes and untold Terminator stories.</li><li>Shoot, sneak and escape the T-1000’s blades in a wide array of levels, and lead the Resistance as John Connor in critical Future War missions.</li><li>Battle against the full force of Cyberdyne and Skynet’s arsenal, with multiple enemy types and adrenaline-pumping boss fights to take on.</li><li>See the world of T2: Judgment Day like never before with detailed 2D <a title="Companies > sprite [19 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/sprite">sprite</a> artwork of your favorite characters and scenes.</li><li>Enjoy a cinematic soundtrack featuring recrafted music from the legendary T2 score and all-new compositions.</li><li>Aim for the highest rank in each level to reign supreme on your high score table and achieve arcade immortality.</li><li>Mix things up with multiple different game modes to choose from: Story Mode, <a title="Platforms > Arcade [378 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/arcade">Arcade</a> Mode, Infinite Mode, Boss Rush, Mother of the Future and Level Training!</li></ul></blockquote></div></div><br/><br/>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/terminator-2d-no-fate-delayed-to-october-31]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
